org.akubraproject.tck
Class TCKTestSuite

java.lang.Object
  org.akubraproject.tck.AbstractTests
      org.akubraproject.tck.TCKTestSuite

public abstract class TCKTestSuite
extends AbstractTests

A suite of unit tests for Akubra stores.

The tests are assigned, and depend on, various groups. All tests here depend on (directly or indirectly) the group "init", and there is one dummy test in that group; all tests that manipulate blobs (create, delete, modify, move) are in the "manipulatesBlobs" group; there is one test in the "post" group, and that test depends on the "manipulatesBlobs" to ensure it is run after all blob manipulations are completed. Additional there are three groups that represent the entity they're testing: "store", "connection", and "blob".

Subclasses of this must implement at least getInvalidId. Additionally, many stores will probably want to override createId and getPrefixFor in order to create URI's which are understood by the store.

For stores that don't support all modify operations, various flags can be passed to the constructor indicating what is supported. This works fine for the transactional, id-gen, and move-to flags; however, create, delete, and list-ids are needed throughout the tests. For stores that don't support one or more of these latter flags you must also override one or more of createBlob and deleteBlob to create and delete the underlying resources, and assertNoBlobs and listBlobs for verifying things got cleaned up properly.

Method Detail

createId

protected URI createId(String name)
Create an id for the given name. Usually this will incorporate the given name as part of the URI itself (e.g. by appending it to a fixed prefix), but for stores that can't do this (e.g. a read-only store) they can return an arbitrary URI. This must return different URI's for different names and the same URI for the same name, at least for the duration of each test.

The default implementation returns URI.create("urn:akubra-tck:" + name).

Parameters:
name - the URI's "name"
Returns:
the URI
See Also:
getPrefixFor(java.lang.String)

getPrefixFor

protected String getPrefixFor(String name)
Get the URI prefix for the given name. This is used by the tests to list all blobs created by the test in order to verify things got cleaned up. The name passed in here will be a prefix of the names passed to previous createId(java.lang.String) calls. The expectation is that if createId is overriden then so must this method. In any case the implementation of this method must figure out an appropriate prefix to return that will include all created id's (in the current test).

The default implementation returns "urn:akubra-tck:" + name.

Parameters:
name - the URI's "name"
Returns:
the prefix
